People 50Â years of age and older with one or more chronic health conditions were non-randomly recruited using community outreach methods. The inclusion and exclusion criteria are listed in Table 1. We aimed to recruit 120 individuals who met inclusion criteria and signed the IRB-approved informed consent to participate [60 in each group]. As a pragmatic trial with fixed grant funding for the study, we wanted to ensure that our proposed, efficient sample size had adequate power to detect small effects [20]. Our sample size calculation was based on our regression model that accounts for using all three time points in a single analysis. Using this model at a 5% alpha-level test, our proposed sample size of 120 participants has an 80% power to detect an effect size of 0.07, considered a small effect. Table 1
